extends ../layouts/2col.pug

block append config
  - var pageTitle = 'Navs & tabs';
  - var skipMenu = true;

block content
  .card
    .card-body
      h3 Base nav
      p Navigation available in Bootstrap share general markup and styles, from the base <code>.nav</code> class to the active and disabled states. Swap modifier classes to switch between each style.
      p The base <code>.nav</code> component is built with flexbox and provide a strong foundation for building all types of navigation components. It includes some style overrides (for working with lists), some link padding for larger hit areas, and basic disabled styling.

      .bd-example
        ul.nav
          li.nav-item
            a.nav-link.active(aria-current='page' href='#') Active
          li.nav-item
            a.nav-link(href='#') Link
          li.nav-item
            a.nav-link(href='#') Link
          li.nav-item
            a.nav-link.disabled(aria-disabled='true') Disabled

      pre
        code.language-html
          | &lt;ul class="nav"&gt;
          |   &lt;li class="nav-item"&gt;
          |     &lt;a class="nav-link active" aria-current="page" href="#"&gt;Active&lt;/a&gt;
          |   &lt;/li&gt;
          |   &lt;li class="nav-item"&gt;
          |     &lt;a class="nav-link" href="#"&gt;Link&lt;/a&gt;
          |   &lt;/li&gt;
          |   &lt;li class="nav-item"&gt;
          |     &lt;a class="nav-link" href="#"&gt;Link&lt;/a&gt;
          |   &lt;/li&gt;
          |   &lt;li class="nav-item"&gt;
          |     &lt;a class="nav-link disabled" aria-disabled="true"&gt;Disabled&lt;/a&gt;
          |   &lt;/li&gt;
          | &lt;/ul&gt;

      p Classes are used throughout, so your markup can be super flexible. Use <code>&lt;ul&gt;</code>s like above, <code>&lt;ol&gt;</code> if the order of your items is important, or roll your own with a <code>&lt;nav&gt;</code> element. Because the <code>.nav</code> uses <code>display: flex</code>, the nav links behave the same as nav items would, but without the extra markup.

      .bd-example
        nav.nav
          a.nav-link.active(aria-current='page' href='#') Active
          a.nav-link(href='#') Link
          a.nav-link(href='#') Link
          a.nav-link.disabled(aria-disabled='true') Disabled

      pre
        code.language-html
          | &lt;nav class="nav"&gt;
          |   &lt;a class="nav-link active" aria-current="page" href="#"&gt;Active&lt;/a&gt;
          |   &lt;a class="nav-link" href="#"&gt;Link&lt;/a&gt;
          |   &lt;a class="nav-link" href="#"&gt;Link&lt;/a&gt;
          |   &lt;a class="nav-link disabled" aria-disabled="true"&gt;Disabled&lt;/a&gt;
          | &lt;/nav&gt;

      h3 Available styles
      p Change the style of <code>.nav</code>s component with modifiers and utilities. Mix and match as needed, or build your own.

      h3 Horizontal alignment
      p Change the horizontal alignment of your nav with flexbox utilities. By default, navs are left-aligned, but you can easily change them to center or right-aligned.
      p Centered with <code>.justify-content-center</code>:

      .bd-example
        ul.nav.justify-content-center
          li.nav-item
            a.nav-link.active(aria-current='page' href='#') Active
          li.nav-item
            a.nav-link(href='#') Link
          li.nav-item
            a.nav-link(href='#') Link
          li.nav-item
            a.nav-link.disabled(aria-disabled='true') Disabled

      pre
        code.language-html
          | &lt;ul class="nav justify-content-center"&gt;
          |   &lt;li class="nav-item"&gt;
          |     &lt;a class="nav-link active" aria-current="page" href="#"&gt;Active&lt;/a&gt;
          |   &lt;/li&gt;
          |   &lt;li class="nav-item"&gt;
          |     &lt;a class="nav-link" href="#"&gt;Link&lt;/a&gt;
          |   &lt;/li&gt;
          |   &lt;li class="nav-item"&gt;
          |     &lt;a class="nav-link" href="#"&gt;Link&lt;/a&gt;
          |   &lt;/li&gt;
          |   &lt;li class="nav-item"&gt;
          |     &lt;a class="nav-link disabled" aria-disabled="true"&gt;Disabled&lt;/a&gt;
          |   &lt;/li&gt;
          | &lt;/ul&gt;

      p Right-aligned with <code>.justify-content-end</code>:

      .bd-example
        ul.nav.justify-content-end
          li.nav-item
            a.nav-link.active(aria-current='page' href='#') Active
          li.nav-item
            a.nav-link(href='#') Link
          li.nav-item
            a.nav-link(href='#') Link
          li.nav-item
            a.nav-link.disabled(aria-disabled='true') Disabled

      pre
        code.language-html
          | &lt;ul class="nav justify-content-end"&gt;
          |   &lt;li class="nav-item"&gt;
          |     &lt;a class="nav-link active" aria-current="page" href="#"&gt;Active&lt;/a&gt;
