          |   &lt;/li&gt;
          |   &lt;li class="nav-item"&gt;
          |     &lt;a class="nav-link disabled" aria-disabled="true"&gt;Disabled&lt;/a&gt;
          |   &lt;/li&gt;
          | &lt;/ul&gt;

      h3 Vertical
      p Stack your navigation by changing the flex item direction with the <code>.flex-column</code> utility. Need to stack them on some viewports but not others? Use the responsive versions (e.g., <code>.flex-sm-column</code>).

      .bd-example
        ul.nav.flex-column
          li.nav-item
            a.nav-link.active(aria-current='page' href='#') Active
          li.nav-item
            a.nav-link(href='#') Link
          li.nav-item
            a.nav-link(href='#') Link
          li.nav-item
            a.nav-link.disabled(aria-disabled='true') Disabled

      pre
        code.language-html
          | &lt;ul class="nav flex-column"&gt;
          |   &lt;li class="nav-item"&gt;
          |     &lt;a class="nav-link active" aria-current="page" href="#"&gt;Active&lt;/a&gt;
          |   &lt;/li&gt;
